-size <width>x<height>{+offset}
width and height of the image
Use this option to specify the width and height of raw images whose dimensions
are unknown such as GRAY, RGB, orCMYK. In addition to width and height, use
-size with an offset to skip any header information in the image or tell the
number of colors in a MAP image file, (e.g. -size 640x512+256).
For Photo CD images, choose from these sizes:

192x128
384x256
768x512
1536x1024
3072x2048



Finally, use this option to choose a particular resolution layer of a JBIG or
JPEG image (e.g. -size 1024x768).
